      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the compromise is as deep as you suspect, a simple clean install might not be enough, as the root of the issue could be in the foundational firmware or supply chain. The most robust defense is to isolate the machine completely and begin a forensic analysis of the bootloader and kernel integrity. You must assume the operating system itself is untrustworthy and look for hardware-level verification methods to establish a truly clean baseline.",
